fields.title: Two Sum
fields.subtitle: Given an array of integers nums and an integer target, return indices of the two numbers such that they add up to target.
fields.description:
Example 1:

Input: nums = [2,7,11,15], target = 9
Output: [0,1]
Explanation: Because nums[0] + nums[1] == 9, we return [0, 1].
Example 2:

Input: nums = [3,2,4], target = 6
Output: [1,2]
Example 3:

Input: nums = [3,3], target = 6
Output: [0,1]
 

Constraints:

2 <= nums.length <= 104
-109 <= nums[i] <= 109
-109 <= target <= 109
Only one valid answer exists.
 

Follow-up: Can you come up with an algorithm that is less than O(n2) time complexity?

fields.title: Longest Common Prefix
fields.subtitle: Write a function to find the longest common prefix string amongst an array of strings.  If there is no common prefix, return an empty string "".
fields.description:
Example 1:

Input: strs = ["flower","flow","flight"]
Output: "fl"
Example 2:

Input: strs = ["dog","racecar","car"]
Output: ""
Explanation: There is no common prefix among the input strings.
 

Constraints:

1 <= strs.length <= 200
0 <= strs[i].length <= 200
strs[i] consists of only lowercase English letters.

fields.title: Number square
fields.subtitle: You are given a Number. You need to return this number in square
fields.description:
Example 1:
Input: number = 4
Output: 16

Example 2:
Input: number = 12
Output: 144 

Example 3:
Input: number = 13
Output: 169

Constraints:
-1000 <= number.length <= 1000
s consists of English letters (lower-case and upper-case), digits (0-9), ' ', '+', '-', and '.'
